{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2013-07-08T21:36:23Z","content":"The latest comments by the Toronto Police Service blaming pedestrians when the victims of reckless and dangerous driving is incredibly disturbing. The Police Service is saying that illegal, dangerous driving has come to be permitted in Toronto, rather than policed. Who has set this direction for policing? Why should our safety and street life be sacrificed in this way? ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Cheryl Lousley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29227349"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:45:12Z","content":"Because I was waiting at that constricted crossing point an hour before this accident and it could have been me. The place was full of kids coming back from the Islands on their second day of  summer holidays and office workers on lunch breaks. All innocently waiting to cross. It is a tragedy and should be reported as such and treated by the Police as such. My heart goes out to all affected, whether hurt or in shock. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Hilary Holden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55608092"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T14:06:17Z","content":"The woman who went through a stop sign and ran me over while biking didn't even get a ticket. Even when there were witnesses. No one cared and I am just learning to walk again after surgery. WTG Toronto...","like_count":1,"author_name":"L S","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3288212"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:19:54Z","content":"As frequent driver, cyclist and pedestrian, I see the roads from many perspectives daily and I have to say that the amount of drivers out there that don't know what they are doing behind a wheel is phenomenal.  Maybe more drivers should speak up about this fact.  Its these drivers that are out there doing ridiculous, illegal, and dangerous moves, not so much the pedestrians or cyclists.  We need to be cracking down on bad driving, not force those walking and cycling or blading or whatever to watch themselves even more than they have to.  Its a zoo out there.","like_count":0,"author_name":"julie rippl","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16650517"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T20:14:25Z","content":"Walking is my preferred way to get around the city, and I shouldn't feel unsafe doing so. I've witnessed countless examples of motorists driving with impatience and aggression. These drivers need to educated to realize the damage that they're capable of causing to pedestrians and cyclists.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin Bell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55963511"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T20:53:49Z","content":"The blame on pedestrians for being pedestrians is unacceptable","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joshua Malinsky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34619499"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:44:40Z","content":"For police to make better judgments and treat people with respect. Don't blame innocent and hurt people. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eric Janiszewski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55754434"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T20:15:00Z","content":"I am a pedestrian, cyclist and as-infrequently-as-possible driver. I was disappointed but not surprised by the police comments last week.  Change is tough for some -- but sharing  the road in a respectful, safe manner will come!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beth Clune","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55909110"},{"created_at":"2013-07-12T15:27:36Z","content":"It is unconscionable to blame the victims of this tragedy, either directly or by proxy, for what happened. Attitudes towards various modes of transportation in this city have become increasingly polarized and we need to stop it and approach the issues in a rational, informed way. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Matthew Browning","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/49985447"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:28:06Z","content":"In any collision between a car and a pedestrian, the pedestrian loses.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Winchester","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1984785"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T18:43:45Z","content":"\"On July 3rd, ten people were injured when two cars jumped the sidewalk on Lakeshore Boulevard. The Toronto Police Service responded by casting blame on the victims in confusing and incorrect statements...We ask the Toronto Police Service to consider the outcome of these messages. The negative impact is clear: it puts the TPS in an adversarial relationship with law-abiding citizens while normalizing unlawful behaviour.  We ask the Toronto Police to work with us as partners in this, as people affected by it, and as people whose experience, knowledge, and investment in our City are a necessary part of the an effective strategy.  We would like to be part of the solution.  Why are you treating us like the problem?\"","like_count":0,"author_name":"Liz Crawford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7483948"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T04:40:06Z","content":"This is a ridiculous way of thinking! Hard to believe it could possibly be real and that someone believes it is right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ainsley Moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16220640"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T19:30:08Z","content":"I'm tired of pedestrians and cyclists being regarded as collateral damage whenever there is an incident like this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jun Nogami","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1786845"},{"created_at":"2013-08-07T23:22:59Z","content":"I visit Toronto frquently and hardly ever drive in the city unless I'm just arriving or leaving. I had a narrow escape at Yonge and King Edward a couple of years ago, and another in late Feb when I was walking from the train station to pick up an airport shuttle. I'm not used to the city so I'm always very careful to cross at crosswalks and wait for the signs. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Vyse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58959371"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T14:21:45Z","content":"A family member dies in a bicycle accident","like_count":0,"author_name":"Monica Bologa","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55884863"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T19:37:33Z","content":"tired of being viewed by the city drivers as an obstruction- I am traffic","like_count":0,"author_name":"andrew aitken","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27408838"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T01:59:03Z","content":"Cities and roads are for everyone to enjoy. This can only work when cars are driving responsibly and vulnerable road users are safe and not made to feel as if they are taking their life into their own hands if they choose to share the road with cars. It is unacceptable to blame lawful victims of car recklessness.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arwen Birch","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9510293"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T19:45:40Z","content":"Highway traffic act: \r\nPedestrian right of way\r\n(28)  Every pedestrian who lawfully enters a roadway in order to cross may continue the crossing as quickly as reasonably possible despite a change in the indication he or she is facing and, for purposes of the crossing, has the right of way over vehicles. R.S.O. 1990, c. H.8, s. 144 (28).\r\n\r\nThe pedestrian has right of way EVEN IF the light changes to red, let alone is counting down. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lloyd Alter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7340314"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:21:05Z","content":"Tired of the media and police ignoring and downplaying dangerous/careless driving and putting the blame on the victims.","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Schwartz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7850896"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T04:33:36Z","content":"Fairness matters. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karly Malpiede","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55981172"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T16:26:21Z","content":"Police have been hired and are paid to serve all of the community, not just the motorized community. Any cop who forgets that should be fired. We owe such strong action to the more vulnerable members of us: the ones that are young or old, or of lesser financial means, or just trying to create a better world by not lugging a ton of steel with them when they move about town.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erhard kraus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38829866"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T21:28:25Z","content":"Pedestrians are all the people of the city. We should be given priority, instead of being treated as nuisances interfering with the \"important\" traffic.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Helen Riley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7309314"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T21:02:53Z","content":"Pedestrians should be the priority since they have the least protection. Lower the speed limits on city streets.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Murray Lumley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3006075"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T06:40:35Z","content":"Pedestrians are people too!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gordon Yarley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2973849"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T01:28:20Z","content":"I've never had the sense the TPS has treated dangerous driving -- at least dangerous driving around pedestrians and cyclists -- seriously. As a Toronto pedestrian, I developed a pretty conservative instinct which legal maneuvers I couldn't make because it would put me at risk, which as the petitioner points out, shouldn't be necessary. Pedestrians represent a huge share of downtown traffic, yet are too often treated as obstacles rather than equals.\r\n\r\nThe vast majority of drivers are safe and prudent, and pedestrians/cyclists are far from perfect, but the problem in these accidents were the drivers, and the police shouldn't be blaming the victims like this.\r\n\r\n(I recently moved to Montreal, but lived in Toronto from 2007-2013.)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Grant Heaslip","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/grantheaslip"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T16:01:41Z","content":"Because I should not have to fear for my life when walking on the sidewalk...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Enrique Cerini","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55755298"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T23:24:46Z","content":"We ALL have to get out of our cars and walk eventually!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Alton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7320535"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T19:39:10Z","content":"because its right","like_count":0,"author_name":"blair brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55767501"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T13:42:11Z","content":"I am a pedestrian, a cyclist and a driver. I want all of us to be as safe as possible!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Philippa King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55882413"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T21:17:27Z","content":" This is a problem common o all Canadian cities, and needs to b corrected. Hw did the 'rights of the car' beck greater than the rights of people? Of course the are not, nd this misconception must be challenged at ever instance.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Doug Moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7080857"},{"created_at":"2013-07-13T21:07:20Z","content":"It's unreasonable to expect pedestrians to take the blame for bad driving. What about kids?! I can't imagine these statements would be made by police in other major Canadian cities. Are you in schools teaching kids how to jump out of the way of moving vehicles when THEY have the right to cross? ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sheila  Boudreau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/4984778"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:31:37Z","content":"Cars kill cyclists and pedestrians, cyclists and pedestrians don't kill drivers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle N","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7833834"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T05:57:02Z","content":"I used to live in Toronto. Now I go there to visit family. It is such a great city in so many ways. When I lived there, we did not own a car because we didn't need one. Now it seems that car-use is given preference. I think that people who drive vehicles that weigh tons and move fast should be able to control them. At the very least they should not harm law-abiding pedestrians and bicyclists. Further, I think they should be watchful for those who might not be where they \"should\" be. I drive a car, but I also ride my bicycle and walk. I always strive to considerately share the road. I think that is a culture worth fostering in Toronto and elsewhere.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathryn S. Downing","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1776501"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T00:51:54Z","content":"I am cyclist!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Radha Nagaratnam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45061135"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T18:06:07Z","content":"My daughter bikes in Toronto.  I'm afraid every day.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meredith Thompson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12841053"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T12:16:02Z","content":"I visited ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Concera Embury","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22800623"},{"created_at":"2013-07-11T08:43:39Z","content":"Blaming the victim is just plain wrong!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Philip Hartung","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56114462"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T20:27:39Z","content":"Cyclists and pedestrians are the more physically vulnerable users of our shared space. We all must endeavour to share this space safely. In the case of tragic \"accidents\", we have failed to adequately protect the vulnerable. We should NEVER blame the victim!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Oster","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27538085"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T01:54:27Z","content":"Let's create safe streets for all users, and ensure that those who place others in danger are held responsible for their behaviour. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennie Worden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55848211"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T22:00:04Z","content":"As a pedestrian I am nearly killed by reckless drivers who run red light, while I obey all laws. I am a senior citizen and for the police to actually blame the victims of this accidents is an abomination. How dare you blame the pedestrians who were on the sidewalk! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kris King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17266573"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T16:11:03Z","content":"I am a pedestrian, cyclist and occasional driver. I'm signing because I expect the police to help drivers share the road with pedestrians, cyclists (and mounted officers), not scare pedestrians and cyclists into treating our roads as if they were highways.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Yap","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29549431"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T12:10:38Z","content":"As a cyclist, pedestrian and occasional driver, I strive to be as careful and courteous as possible.  We as torontonions are slowly losing our good natured cooperation.  This is why we need Complete Streets.","like_count":0,"author_name":"isaac kay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39498231"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T18:28:36Z","content":"It seems to me that the person in charge of the vehicle with the most potential for damage should be the most cautious, and not focusing on their behaviour lets them off the hook in a way I find distasteful.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Blake Winton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48003264"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T18:11:28Z","content":"Because when someone in a car places a part of that car in the path of human being, causing injury to that human being, it should be reported by the police. How do you justify the willful ignorance of neglect on a part of these drivers, particularly when there is often great harm done to those injured. It should either be regarded as a vehicular crime, or outright assault. Either way, it is a police officer's duty to record and report these crimes.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Josh Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55900514"},{"created_at":"2013-07-11T05:56:05Z","content":"We all need to share the roads and look out for each other.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mark Jull","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40838716"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T12:25:29Z","content":"I am a driver, pedestrian and sometimes use a bicycle, and facing these issues ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joseph Bauer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55878072"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T13:55:40Z","content":"Because a city must be safe for living. Cars move too fast and mow down pedestrians and cyclists for no other reason than the infrastructure allows them to. Let's make our cities safe for ALL.","like_count":0,"author_name":"S J","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43926279"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T01:51:00Z","content":"North American car politics are earning themselves a chapter in some of our most tragic history books.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Arancibia","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55782721"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T14:12:02Z","content":"I'm a law abiding cyclist and am tired of the way we are treated by Toronto Police Services, while auto drivers are allowed cart blanche on our streets!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole  Heater","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12854004"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T16:34:27Z","content":"We need to save lives. Pedestrians are most vulnerable and should be top priority","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gil Penalosa","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55757429"},{"created_at":"2013-07-31T13:38:20Z","content":"Walking is my mode of transport in the City of Toronto. I see dangerous situations for pedestrians almost every day and feel that it shouldn't be so. Let's focus some attention on this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pat Doherty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42002061"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T21:48:58Z","content":"I'm appalled at TPS's attitude toward the most vulnerable commuters on the road in favour of the most entitled. The quote from Officer Smith about pedestrians in the Lakeshore/Bay St accident takes the cake. How was even one pedestrian to blame for a car turning left in front of another? Yet, that's the spin.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janet Langdon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7522242"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T02:21:02Z","content":"In a civilized society, we should never tolerate the sort of might-is-right cognitive bias that dominates how we think of our roads. The focus of the police needs to be on those creating the dangerous situation we have today for our more vulnerable road users. As a victim of a hit and run who saw no justice or even an attempt by police to help me identify the perpetrator, this issue is extremely important to me. I don't live in Toronto, but this sort of thing happens all over North America every day and I'm sick to death of it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Hagstrom","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2524582"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T01:02:34Z","content":"If the attitude of the police in Toronto is not changed, it can spread all over Canada. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Debus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7851667"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T23:24:54Z","content":"1) We lost a dear friend to a biking/car collision, 2) We want to be able to bike safely on the streets, 3) A city where people cannot safely ride bikes is a city condemned to environmental and social issues","like_count":0,"author_name":"Adriana Vasilescu","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55840999"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:33:51Z","content":"Drivers in this city need to be held accountable for their behaviour. If anything else was causing this many deaths in a week, we'd be outraged. I'm tired of Toronto acting like cyclists and pedestrian death by car is an unavoidable fact of life. Something can be done and it takes the cooperation of the police force.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tara Knott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55753904"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:24:54Z","content":"I'm tired of the constant victim-blaming of pedestrians by TPS. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Arr","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55760522"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T12:53:49Z","content":"My friend was murdered on a bike and the limp-dick Toronto Police did nothing. But god forbid one of THEM gets run over by a snoplow......","like_count":0,"author_name":"aryeh smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55746153"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T14:12:29Z","content":"Let's start putting the blame where it belongs: distracted and careless drivers. Cyclists and pedestrians need the service and protection of Toronto Police, not their blame.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sonia Serba","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7301811"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T10:27:12Z","content":"It's time to change the predominant car culture.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Yee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2638459"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T18:50:10Z","content":"Who trains cops? We must set higher standards. We should not tolerate such ignorance.","like_count":0,"author_name":"angela bischoff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5170401"},{"created_at":"2013-07-12T15:16:30Z","content":"I was nearly doored by a policeman this morning who then laughed and mocked me.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Siobhan Ozege","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47555417"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T04:02:28Z","content":"As a law abiding pedestrian, I have a target painted on my back.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Reid Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50116096"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:53:49Z","content":"Cyclists and pedestrians have a right to partake of their chosen mode of transportation in safety, without constant fear of the repercussion from poor drivers.  Bringing public awareness to the fact that it is poor and/or illegal driving that is the problem - not the mere presence of cyclists or pedestrians - will hopefully encourage the Toronto Police Service and others to focus on the root cause of these accidents, rather than blaming the victims.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jamie Drake","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46554659"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:26:14Z","content":"One would think an unprotected pedestrian surely has the right-of-way on a pedestrian cross-walk (and definitely, on the sidewalk!), regardless of the Light position.  Senior Citizens and the Disabled (being one myself) require a longer time to cross...\r\n\r\nPlease adjust your mindset/thinking to actually project the proper attitude required for those who Protect and Serve.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration regarding this important issue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"William Devitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35788549"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:34:22Z","content":"Because I am a human being. I need no other reason, the cult of the car has to be reined in.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shane Marx","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43662998"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T13:28:09Z","content":"As a 50 yr old man born in Toronto, I am concerned at the direction and adverse effects of these recent statements and their larger portent. Please respect the public and serve and protect us.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Douglas Catty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34127085"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T16:24:05Z","content":"Traffic control signals and pedestrian control signals - 144.\r\n\r\nYielding to pedestrians\r\n\r\n(7) When under this section a driver is permitted to proceed, the driver shall yield the right of way to pedestrians lawfully within a crosswalk. R.S.O. 1990, c. H.8, s. 144 (7).","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Bailey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52499829"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T15:49:44Z","content":"I too have been perplexed, disappointed and appalled at the constant \"victim-blaming\" by the Toronto Police... it is time that everyone stop acting as if cyclists, pedestrians and cars are natural enemies. We share this City - so let's start working collaberatively.  First and foremost that means STOP blaming the victims and start addressing the real miscreants!","like_count":0,"author_name":"sheenagh murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2692032"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T18:38:39Z","content":"I am a frequent pedestrian. I walk just about everywhere I need to go. If I'm not safe on the sidewalks, please don't blame me, but blame the drivers who are on the sidewalks with the pedestrians.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Hamel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52986182"},{"created_at":"2013-07-12T02:22:00Z","content":"Being a pedestrian in Toronto is dangerous and challenging at the best of times. We all make mistakes but carelessness by drivers kills others and it needs to be treated seriously, not implicitly condoned or treated as inevitable.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gary Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56176245"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T09:12:02Z","content":"As both a driver and frequent walker in this city, I believe pedestrians shouldn't be held to blame in situations beyond their control (and when they are in the right, legally)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christina Bindon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52565717"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:32:46Z","content":"Police are paid public servants. What they are doing is outrageous. Not only are they destroying the faith of their own residents, they are  giving the world a good reason to stay away - thus killing their own economy. Who would want to visit a place where they are not safe?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sophia Marx","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9039971"},{"created_at":"2013-07-31T18:55:21Z","content":"Because there is a huge need for police reform in this city. The police are killing people without just cause. - either by guns and tasers or by misinformation and cover ups. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marusya Bociurkiw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45122367"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T21:19:04Z","content":"When did cars start to have \"rights\" over people? This is insane. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fiona McMurran","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1212047"},{"created_at":"2013-07-12T15:36:29Z","content":"I bike every day and want to be able to trust my Police Service to ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Pearsell-Ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44536753"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T05:04:29Z","content":"My hope is that the Toronto Police Service might give some consideration to the fact that it is drivers, whose inattention carries lethal consequences, not pedestrians and cyclists who should be at the center of this focus on safe streets. We have to make it substantially harder for people to become drivers and to maintain their licenses. The normalization of drivers as the only ones who are in transit from one place to another is problematic and demands challenge.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christopher Wulff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7258128"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T22:55:24Z","content":"Streets are not made for cars, they are made for citizens, however they may travel. It is way past time to jerk the Toronto Police from their squad cars and put them all on foot or bicycle so they know the neighborhood they police and the people in that neighborhood. Squad cars are for emergencies, not patrol.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bruce MacLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6868216"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T22:34:15Z","content":"Toronto is slipping into the dark ages when it comes to car/bike/pedestrian relations, and space allocation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"abigail pugh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58157955"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T23:29:22Z","content":"I am most often a pedestrian and a cyclist. I am as alert as I can be, but I cannot compensate for inattentive or impaired drivers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"pat anderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1851861"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T20:47:04Z","content":"Highway traffic act says pedestrians have right of way even if the light has changed, let alone when the countdown is going. Pedestrian right of way\r\n(28) Every pedestrian who lawfully enters a roadway in order to cross may continue the crossing as quickly as reasonably possible despite a change in the indication he or she is facing and, for purposes of the crossing, has the right of way over vehicles. R.S.O. 1990, c. H.8, s. 144 (28).","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jake Allderdice","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10847089"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T23:55:55Z","content":"Like most people in the world, I am a pedestrian some of the time -- I should not have to take extreme measures to avoid being hit by deranged drivers!  The police need to have the right attitude about this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nathanael Nerode","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2686651"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T03:03:50Z","content":"I am a cyclist and pedestrian and a motorist.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susanne Marquardt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55851506"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T23:20:05Z","content":"I am a responsible cyclist and pedestrian.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Travis Sanderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32227335"},{"created_at":"2013-07-10T03:37:28Z","content":"I am getting more and more angry at the victimization of pedestrians and cyclists. I use all modes of transport, including driving. Guess what - when I drive, I drive slowly, respectfully, and very very carefully. Why? Because I'm driving a two-ton potentially lethal weapon. A kid could run out in front of me on a neighbourhood street. Anything could happen. I ask Chief Blair to team up with the city and with Chief Medical Officer Dr. McKeown to please start a campaign to grow a culture of respect on the streets instead of entitlement by drivers. Drivers are almost ALways speeding now, and I want to see speed limits reduced AND ENFORCED. Thank you.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carina Cojeen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7273378"},{"created_at":"2013-07-30T20:54:35Z","content":"Because I use all modes of transport at different times, I'd like to feel as safe as reasonably possible while doing so, safe from those who put their own wants, needs, and ignorance ahead of public safety.","like_count":0,"author_name":"William Latanville","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/546228"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T13:22:44Z","content":"Because cars are deadly and we forget this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"ali berkok","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3110514"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T13:50:04Z","content":"I am an active cyclist and pedestrian who chooses not to drive in Toronto. I hear plenty about the \"War on Cars\", but it's clear there are an unacceptable number of casualties on the side of those who bike/walk, at the hands of drivers who are able to duck responsibility in the eyes of law enforcement. I am now fighting back in self-defense.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kira Hall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28207287"},{"created_at":"2013-07-17T05:15:35Z","content":"I'm a car driver, a bus rider, a pedestrian, and a cyclist. I've yet to see or hear of a person killing a car or a bus in a collision. Therefore cars and buses and trucks, in other words, motorized vehicles should always be presumed guilty in accidents that involve pedestrians or cyclists, because they are the only ones with power/capability of destruction in the interchange.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Anderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7897205"},{"created_at":"2013-07-07T06:06:50Z","content":"Because I am a law-abiding pedestrian, cyclist, and driver and think the TPS needs to address the source of the problem, not the consequence. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ariane Tisseur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38350634"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T00:28:17Z","content":"I was charged $500 after being hit by a vehicle on my bike while crossing on a green light.  The driver got away with out any charges. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Rogalla","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52509585"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T14:55:34Z","content":"I cycle through downtown Toronto every day, 20 km round trip, and there needs to be a paradigm shift regarding what constitutes traffic. The police seem to be supporting the right of cars to careen through the downtown at lethal speeds while the rest of us are supposed to get out of the way. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Denise Denning","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55751945"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T17:55:22Z","content":"Why is this important, TPS? \r\n\r\nTo \"serve & protect\" is your Hippocratic Oath. When serving & protecting the most vulnerable on your beat isn't the baseline of your policing culture, then you have quit your job. You have forfeited your Oath. You have done little more than show up at the office to slap on fancy-tech aggro gear and collect a paycheque (paid for by us, the vulnerable you decline to serve & protect). \r\n\r\nPolicing isn't about \"catching the bad guys.\" Policing is about protecting the vulnerable by prevention, advocacy, policy change, and paying attention. In a city with millions of vehicular weapons, almost all weighing at least a tonne, bicyclists and pedestrians are vulnerable. \r\n\r\nIf you can't protect the vulnerable, then find another line of work.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Astrid Idlewild","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55762299"},{"created_at":"2013-07-31T19:12:40Z","content":"I often cross Dundas West by a pedestrian crossing close to the Wallace Street foot bridge. Cars rarely stop and the police seem not to care.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nils-Petter Lagerl\u00f6f","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58277896"},{"created_at":"2013-07-08T21:35:36Z","content":"Surprised and saddened to see this misstep out of Toronto.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leo Masic","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55914643"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T03:07:24Z","content":"Blaming the victim has to stop.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laurel Bowman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30760476"},{"created_at":"2013-07-06T19:36:22Z","content":"More economically and environmentally viable sources of transportation should be encouraged. Automobiles should be second to pedestrians and cyclists.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aidan Muller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35069062"},{"created_at":"2013-07-09T01:35:41Z","content":"Police should enforce safer driving to protect innocent pedestrians. This article is shameful and promotes dangerous driving and road rage against vulnerable pedestrians.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jan Gates","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7316569"}]}
